def central_difference(f, x, h):
    valor_derivado =  (f(x+h)-f(x))/h
    return valor_derivado
    
def squared(x): 
    cuadratica=x**2
    return cuadratica

cd201=central_difference(squared, 2, 0.1)
cd2001=central_difference(squared, 2, 0.01)
cd20001=central_difference(squared, 2, 0.001)

print(f"The derivative of f(x) = x^2 at x = 2 using h = 0.1 is {cd201}.")
print(f"The derivative of f(x) = x^2 at x = 2 using h = 0.01 is {cd2001}.")
print(f"The derivative of f(x) = x^2 at x = 2 using h = 0.001 is {cd20001}.")

The derivative of f(x) = x^2 at x = 2 using h = 0.1 is 4.100000000000001.
The derivative of f(x) = x^2 at x = 2 using h = 0.01 is 4.009999999999891.
The derivative of f(x) = x^2 at x = 2 using h = 0.001 is 4.000999999999699.
